{"title_page": "2020 Tablighi Jamaat coronavirus hotspot in Delhi", "text_new": "{{pp-protected|small=yes}}\n{{Unreliable sources|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox event\n| date                     = 1\u201321 March 2020\n| venue                    = [[Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]]\n| location                 = [[Nizamuddin West]], [[Delhi]]\n| type                     = Religious congregation\n| participants             = 4500 \u2013 9000\n| organisers               = [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]]\n| website                  = \n}}\n\nA [[Tablighi Jamaat]] religious congregation that took place in Delhi's [[Nizamuddin Markaz Mosque]] in early March 2020 was a [[Coronavirus disease 2019|coronavirus]] [[super-spreader]] event,<ref name=\"WaPoSuperSpreader2Apr\">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/asia_pacific/india-coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-delhi/2020/04/02/abdc5af0-7386-11ea-ad9b-254ec99993bc_story.html|title=India confronts its first coronavirus 'super-spreader' \u2014 a Muslim missionary group with more than 400 members infected|last=Slater|first=Joanna|last2=Masih|first2=Niha|last3=Irfan|first3=Shams|date=2 April 2020|newspaper=Washington Post}}</ref> with more than 4,000 confirmed cases<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/coronavirus-tablighi-jamaat-30-per-cent-of-coronavirus-cases-linked-to-delhi-mosque-event-government-2206163|title=30 Per Cent Of Coronavirus Cases Linked To Delhi Mosque Event: Government|date=4 April 2020|work=NDTV}}</ref> and at least 27 deaths linked to the event reported across the country. Over 9,000 missionaries may have attended the congregation, with the majority being from various states of India,<ref name=\"TOI 2 April\">\n{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: About 9,000 Tablighi Jamaat members, primary contacts quarantined in country, MHA says |newspaper=The Times of India |agency=PTI |date=2 April 2020 |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/coronavirus-about-9000-tablighi-jamaat-members-primary-contacts-quarantined-in-country-mha-says/articleshow/74948832.cms}}\n</ref><ref name=\"HT 2 April\">\n{{cite news |title=How Nizamuddin markaz became Covid-19 hotspot; more than 8,000 attendees identified |newspaper=Hindustan Times |date=2 April 2020 |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/how-nizamuddin-markaz-became-a-hotspot-for-covid-19-8-000-people-identified/story-zedKlaDNTPpbDLdMsgExAM.html}}\n</ref> and 960 attendees from 40 foreign countries.<ref>\n{{cite news |title=379 Indonesians among foreigners from 40 countries attended Tablighi Jamaat gathering: Sources |url=https://www.aninews.in/news/national/general-news/379-indonesians-among-foreigners-from-40-countries-attended-tablighi-jamaat-gathering-sources20200403152720/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=ANI}}\n</ref> On 18 April, 4,291 confirmed cases of COVID-19 linked to this event by the Union Health Ministry represented a third of all the confirmed cases of India.<ref name=\"ABP 18 April\">\n{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat Responsible For 30% Total Coronavirus Cases In India: Health Ministry |author=ABP News Bureau |newspaper=ABP News |date=18 April 2020 |url=https://news.abplive.com/news/india/tablighi-jamaat-responsible-for-30-total-coronavirus-cases-in-india-health-ministry-1201263}}\n</ref><ref name=\"PTI 18 April\">\n{{cite news |author=PTI |title=Coronavirus &#124; Nearly 4,300 cases were linked to Tablighi Jamaat event, says Health Ministry |date=18 April 2020 |newspaper=The Hindu |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/coronavirus-nearly-4300-cases-were-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-event-says-health-ministry/article31376202.ece }}\n</ref> Around 40,000 people, including Tablighi Jamaat attendees and their contacts, were quarantined across the country.<ref name=\"ABP 18 April\"/>\n\nThe Tablighi Jamaat has received widespread criticism from the Muslim community for holding the congregation despite a ban on public gatherings being issued by the [[Government of Delhi]] on 13 March.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat draws widespread condemnation from Muslim society |url=https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/news/national/academics-among-muslims-condemn-the-act-of-tablighi-jamaat-in-nizamuddin/article31218658.ece |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Hindu Business Line}}</ref>\n\nUnion Minister for Minority Affairs [[Mukhtar Abbas Naqvi]] urged people to not hold the entire Muslim community for one groups crime.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/entire-muslim-community-cant-be-held-responsible-for-one-groups-crime-mukhtar-abbas-naqvi-on-tablighi-jamaat-row/articleshow/75319334.cms |title=Entire Muslim community can't be held responsible for one group's 'crime': Mukhtar Abbas Naqvi on Tablighi Jamaat row|work=Times of India|date=23 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Events==\nThe Nizamuddin Markaz's calendar shows three events scheduled during March: ''Aalmi Mashwara'' (international executive committee meeting)<ref name=Bhat>{{cite web|url=https://www.greaterkashmir.com/news/opinion/not-a-tableegi-virus/|title=Not a Tableegi Virus|author=Raja Muzaffar Bhat|date=3 April 2020|website=Greater Kashmir}}</ref> during 8\u201310 March, and provincial gatherings ''Andhra Pradesh jod'' during 15\u201317 March and ''Tamil Nadu jod'' during 22\u201324 March.<ref name=facebook>[https://www.facebook.com/NizamuddinIjtema/ Nizamuddin Ijtema], Facebook page, retrieved 19 April 2020.</ref><ref name=\"delhimarkaz.com\">\n[http://www.delhimarkaz.com/ \"Reconstruction of Ummah\"], delhimarkaz.com, retrieved 19 April 2020.\n</ref><ref name=\"news-communique.com\">{{cite web|url=https://news-communique.com/index.php/2020/04/05/panic-grips-tablighi-jamaat-ijtema-maulana-saad-on-the-run/|title=Panic Grips Tablighi Jamaat Ijtema: Maulana Saad On The Run|date=5 April 2020|website=News-Communique.com}}</ref>{{efn|Media reports have variously mentioned a \"congregation\" held on 11\u201313 March,<ref name=Beg>\n{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/india-news-corona-outbreak-afflicted-by-communal-virus-blaming-tablighi-jamaat-could-be-misdirected/349784|title=Communal Corona? Is It Justified To Blame Tablighi Jamaat For Nizamuddin Outbreak?|first=Mirza Arif|last=Beg|date=31 March 2020|website=Outlook}}\n</ref> 13\u201315 March,<ref name=Mustafa>\n{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/communalism/coronavirus-criminal-liability-of-tablighi-jamaat|title=The Coronavirus Spread and the Criminal Liability of the Tablighi Jamaat|first=Faizan|last=Mustafa|date=16 April 2020|website=The Wire}}\n</ref>\nor other dates, which however do not appear on the Markaz's calendar.}} There is no indication of an ''[[ijtema]]'' held in March.<ref name=\"Mahurkar no\">\n{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/web-exclusive/story/the-new-threat-from-tablighi-jamaat-1661938-2020-04-01|title=Tablighi Jamaat's defiance spreads concern|first=Uday|last=Mahurkar|date=1 April 2020|website=India Today|quote=There was no formal convention as previously believed, but there was a bigger than usual gathering of preachers this month.}}\n</ref> An ''ijtema'' would have been too large a gathering for the Markaz building to hold.<ref name=Bhat/>{{efn|A Delhi provincial ijtema was held during 22\u201324 February at Shahi Eidgah.<ref name=facebook/><ref name=\"delhimarkaz.com\"/><ref name=\"news-communique.com\"/>}}\n\nThe ''Aalmi'' ''Mashwara'' probably attracted 1500 persons from different states of India as well as various countries in Asia and Europe.<ref name=Bhat/> The [[Andhra Pradesh]] gathering would have also attracted similar numbers from Andhra Pradesh, [[Telangana]] and the neighbouring states.<ref name=Mustafa/> In addition to these, the Markaz receives a regular year-round traffic of visitors from India and abroad who come for preaching activity and are dispatched to various locations in India. It is common for them to stop at the Markaz for a few days at the beginning and end of their travel.<ref name=Bhat/>\n\nThe activities at the Markaz apparently went unhindered till 22 March, when a [[Janata curfew]] was observed throughout India at the instance of prime minister [[Narendra Modi]]. At the end of the Janata Curfew, a lockdown came into effect in Delhi. The group said that it was able to move out around 1,500 people on the following days with some difficulty.<ref name=Beg/><ref name=Reuters>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/02/world/asia/02reuters-health-coronavirus-india-islam-insight.html|title=The Religious Retreat That Sparked India's Major Coronavirus Manhunt|date=2 April 2020|work=New York Times|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200403162139/https://www.nytimes.com/reuters/2020/04/02/world/asia/02reuters-health-coronavirus-india-islam-insight.html|archive-date=3 April 2020|agency=Reuters}}</ref> On 24 March, when a nationwide lockdown came into effect, the Markaz received a notice from the [[station house officer|SHO]] of the Hazrat Nizamuddin Police Station (which is the next door neighbour of the Markaz) asking for the closure of the building. The following day, a [[tehsildar]] with a medical team visited the Markaz and many of the visitors were examined. On 26 March, the group was called for a meeting with the [[District Magistrate (India)|District Magistrate]]. From 27 March onward, small groups of visitors were taken for medical check-ups. On 29 March, the Markaz responded to a notice from the [[Assistant Commissioner of Police]] of Lajpat Nagar stating that it had abided by all orders and did not allow any new visitors to enter the premises during the lockdown.<ref name=Beg/><ref name=\"Hindu cordoned off\">{{cite news|last=Trivedi|first=Saurabh|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/coronavirus-200-people-from-nizamuddin-develop-symptoms-area-cordoned-off/article31204617.ece|title=Coronavirus {{!}} 200 people in Nizamuddin develop symptoms; area cordoned off|date=30 March 2020|work=The Hindu}}</ref>\n\nOn 30 March, the authorities evacuated the building and sent about 2300 inmates to hospital wards and quarantines.<ref name=\"WaPoSuperSpreader2Apr\" /> Mawl\u0101na [[Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi]], the head of the Markaz, was not found in the building. He later responded to police enquiries stating that he was self-isolating at an unknown location.\n\n==Government measures==\nDelhi is a [[Union territory|union territory with a legislature]], which in effect means that it has a [[dyarchy#India|divided government]]. Most governmental functions are under the control of the [[Government of Delhi|elected government]], while law and order is under the control of the [[Lieutenant Governor of Delhi|lieutenant governor]]. The [[Delhi Police]] reports directly to the Union Home Ministry, rather than any branch of the Delhi government. The parties in power in Delhi and the Union are rivals, adding to frictions and lack of coordination.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehinducentre.com/the-arena/current-issues/article7367199.ece|title=National Capital Territory of Delhi: Towards a Unique Diarchy (...and Away from a Monarchy)|last=Saikumar|first=Rajgopal|website=The Hindu Centre for Politics and Public Policy|date=30 June 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"IANS blame game\">{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/newsscroll/authorities-playing-blame-game-over-nizamuddin-markaz/1787031|title=Authorities playing blame game over Nizamuddin Markaz|website=Outlook|date=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nFor its part, the Union government ordered thermal screening of passengers arriving from [[Malaysia]], [[Indonesia]] and other Asian countries from the end of February.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.outlookindia.com/website/story/india-news-coronavirus-convid-19-india-airports-to-screen-passengers-from-4-countries-nepal-indonesia-vietnam-and-malaysia/347751|title=Coronavirus: Indian Airports To Now Screen Passengers From Four More Countries Including Nepal|website=Outlook|date=23 February 2020}}</ref> From 4 March, thermal screening was extended to passengers from all countries.<ref name=\"CaravanUnfounded16Apr\">{{cite web|url=https://caravanmagazine.in/politics/modis-speech-unfounded-half-truths-at-best-blatant-denial-of-accountability-at-worst|title=Modi's speech: Unfounded half-truths at best, blatant denial of accountability at worst|last=Penkar|first=Ahan|date=16 April 2020|website=The Caravan}}</ref> None of the foreign attendees of the Tablighi events were caught by these measures.<ref name=\"Mustafa\"/> As of 13 March the central government had maintained that there was no health emergency in the country. There were no restrictions on gatherings until this date.<ref>{{cite news|last=Radhakrishnan|first=Sruthi|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/tablighi-jamaat-and-covid-19-the-story-so-far/article31225065.ece|title=Tablighi Jamaat and COVID-19: The story so far|date=1 April 2020|work=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/government/delhis-nizamuddin-hotspot-coronavirus|title=Questions Remain About How Delhi's Nizamuddin Became a Coronavirus Hotspot|date=31 March 2020|website=The Wire|quote=Going by the spread of the coronavirus, however, it appears that the Delhi government\u2019s advisory itself came too late.}}</ref> Home quarantine for international arrivals was not mandated until 17 March.<ref name=\"CaravanUnfounded16Apr\"/>\n\nOn 13 March, the Delhi government issued an order prohibiting sports gatherings, conferences and seminars with over 200 people.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/covid-19-govt-bans-ipl-in-delhi-till-further-orders/article31058763.ece|title=COVID-19: Govt. bans IPL in Delhi till further orders|date=13 March 2020|work=The Hindu}}</ref> The order has been described as being vaguely worded. A second order was issued on 16 March, banning all gatherings over 50 people. The government also ordered the closure of gyms, clubs and spas.<ref name=\"IANS blame game\"/><ref name=\"Newslaundry\">{{cite web|url=https://www.newslaundry.com/2020/04/01/coronavirus-and-nizamuddin-tv-news-returns-to-bigotry-with-a-bang|title=Coronavirus and Nizamuddin: TV news returns to bigotry with a bang|last=Tiwari|first=Ayush|website=Newslaundry|date=1 April 2020}}</ref> But it was not until 24 March that the Delhi Police sought the closure of the Nizamuddin Markaz.<ref name=\"Hindu cordoned off\"/>\n\nOn 16 March, the same day the Delhi order was issued, ten Indonesians who had attended the ''Aalmi Mashwara'' event in Nizamuddin were being isolated in Hyderabad. Eight of the ten men eventually tested positive for COVID-19. The Home Ministry stated that it informed all the state governments about this development on 21 March.<ref name=\"Wire questions\">{{cite web|url=https://thewire.in/government/delhis-nizamuddin-hotspot-coronavirus|title=Questions Remain About How Delhi's Nizamuddin Became a Coronavirus Hotspot|website=The Wire|date=31 March 2020|quote=Going by the spread of the coronavirus, however, it appears that the Delhi government\u2019s advisory itself came too late.}}</ref> On 21 March again, [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)|Jammu and Kashmir]] officials informed the Union Health Ministry's control room that a 65-year-old patient, who had been to the Nizamuddin Markaz, had tested positive for COVID-19. They said that he must have contracted the virus from Indonesian or [[Thailand|Thai]] Tablighi members at the Markaz. The Health Ministry officials did not act on these alerts.<ref name=\"Hindu identify\">{{cite news|last=Singh|first=Vijaita|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece|title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members|date=31 March 2020|work=The Hindu}}</ref>{{failed verification|reason=Source has nothing about the Health Ministry \"not acting on alerts\"|date=April 2020}}\n\nAs late as 5 April, the government agencies were seen to be busy blaming each other without any agency taking responsibility for the lapses.<ref>\nSaurabh Trivedi, Siddharth Ravi, Nikhil M. Babu, [https://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/who-is-to-blame-for-virus-going-viral-from-nizamuddin/article31264902.ece Who is to blame for virus going viral from Nizamuddin?], The Hindu, 5 April 2020.\n</ref>\n\n==Spread==\nA cluster spread became apparent in the following days as cases traced back to the event were reported in several states. In Telangana, five people who attended the event died on 30 March. Dozens of people tested positive in other places such as Andhra Pradesh, [[Tamil Nadu]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] and [[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]]. State governments scrambled to trace the whereabouts of the attendees.<ref>{{cite news |title=Delhi area under watch: Officials link 5 Telangana deaths to Nizamuddin mosque, trace 1,600 people |url=https://indianexpress.com/article/cities/delhi/parts-of-delhis-nizamuddin-west-cordoned-off-after-covid-19-cases-traced-to-area-6338798/ |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=The Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nAs of 3 April, more than 950 confirmed cases were detected across 14 states and union territories in the country, including 97 percent of the total cases confirmed in the country on 2 and 3 April (647 out of 664 cases).<ref name=ndtv>{{cite news |title=647 COVID-19 Cases In Last 2 Days Linked To Islamic Sect Meet In Delhi |url=https://www.ndtv.com/india-news/647-coronavirus-cases-found-in-last-two-days-linked-to-islamic-sect-gathering-in-delhi-says-governme-2205635 |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=NDTV}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=647 coronavirus positive cases in two days linked to Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/647-coronavirus-positive-cases-in-two-days-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat/articleshow/74967407.cms |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Economic Times}}</ref> Tamil Nadu was the worst affected state, as 364 of the 411 people who tested positive had attended the event.<ref>{{cite news |title=102 new Covid-19 cases in Tamil Nadu; state's tally reaches 411 |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/102-new-covid-19-cases-in-tamil-nadu-state-s-tally-reaches-411-11585922977996.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Livemint}}</ref> 259 of the 386 cases in Delhi<ref>{{cite news |title=2 more deaths in Delhi, one a Tablighi Jamaat man; 93 new Coronavirus cases reported |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/2-more-covid-deaths-in-delhi-one-a-tablighi-jamaat-man-93-new-cases-reported/articleshow/74975751.cms |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Times of India}}</ref> and 140 of the 161 cases in Andhra Pradesh were linked to the event.<ref>{{cite news |title=Covid-19: AP reports first death; 140 of 161 cases linked to Markaz Nizamuddin |url=https://www.livemint.com/news/india/covid-19-ap-reports-first-death-140-of-161-cases-linked-to-markaz-nizamuddin-11585899097389.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Livemint}}</ref> All nine deaths reported in Telangana until 2 April were of people who had returned from the congregation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Three more Covid-19 deaths in Telangana, all linked to Markaz event |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/three-more-covid-19-deaths-in-telangana-all-linked-to-markaz-event/story-X0xlWmGltcOvrQClVdEzAI.html |accessdate=3 April 2020 |work=Hindustan Times}}</ref>\n\nThe Srinagar man who died on 26 March was identified as a [[super-spreader]] as he travelled by road, rail and air from Delhi to Srinagar via Uttar Pradesh, as officials feared that he may have spread it to several people along the way.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Delhi Police books Tablighi Jamaat head as Nizamuddin centre emerges as hotspot; 1,339 workers quarantined, says MHA |url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-delhi-police-books-tablighi-jamaat-head-as-nizamuddin-centre-emerges-as-hotspot-1339-workers-quarantined-says-mha-8211721.html |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Firstpost}}</ref>\n\n===Tracing of attendees===\nBy 2 April, [[Maharashtra]], Telangana and [[Karnataka]] traced down 1,325, 1,064 and 800 attendees of the event respectively.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat: 1,325 of 1,400 attendees traced in State |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/coronavirus-two-from-pune-district-who-went-to-nizamuddin-conclave-test-positive/article31234627.ece |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Hindu}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Nine Delhi returnees die in Telangana, 21 new COVID-19 cases |url=https://punemirror.indiatimes.com/news/india/nine-delhi-returnees-die-in-telangana-21-new-covid-19-cases-reported-in-andhra-pradesh/articleshow/74946154.cms |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=Pune Mirror}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=1,500 from Karnataka attended Tablighi Jamaat |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/karnataka/2020/apr/02/15k-from-ktaka-attended-jamaat-2124607.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref> Tamil Nadu identified and quarantined 1,103 of the 1,500-odd participants from the state.<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: How difficult was tracking the Jamaat event attendees from Tamil Nadu? |url=https://www.deccanherald.com/national/south/coronavirus-how-difficult-was-tracking-the-jamaat-event-attendees-from-tamil-nadu-820525.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=Deccan Herald}}</ref> Andhra Pradesh reportedly detected around 800 of the 1,085 people of the state who attended the congregation.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi attendees' motive under police scanner |url=https://www.sundayguardianlive.com/news/tablighi-attendees-motive-police-scanner |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=The Sunday Guardian}}</ref> Gujarat Police identified 72 attendees from the state who attended the event.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/other-states/72-tabligh-attendees-traced-in-gujarat-one-dead-of-covid-19/article31228520.ece|title=Coronavirus {{!}} 72 Tabligh attendees traced in Gujarat; one dead of COVID-19|date=1 April 2020 |work=The Hindu}}</ref> Uttar Pradesh managed to track and quarantine 1,205 people who participated in the congregation by 5 April.<ref>{{cite news |title=1,205 Tablighi Jamaat attendees quarantined so far in UP: Govt official |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/1205-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-quarantined-uttar-pradesh-1663604-2020-04-05 |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 April, it was reported that the [[Delhi Police]] had found more than 500 foreign preachers \"hiding in 16-17 places\" in the city.<ref>{{cite news |title=Over 500 Foreigners Who Attended Tablighi Jamaat Found Hiding in Delhi Mosques |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/over-500-foreigners-who-attended-tablighi-jamaat-found-hiding-in-delhi-mosques-2563791.html |accessdate=5 April 2020 |work=News18}}</ref>\n\n==Aftermath and action==\nThe Union Home Ministry instructed state governments to track down the 824 foreign attendees of the congregation, asking them to screen, quarantine and deport such individuals.<ref>{{cite news |title=Home Ministry asked States to identify 824 foreign Tablighi members |url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/home-ministry-to-blacklist-800-tablighi-preachers-from-indonesia-for-violation-of-visa-rules/article31214048.ece |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=The Hindu}}</ref> On 2 April, the Home Ministry identified 960 foreigners who took part in the event and blacklisted their visas for violation of [[The Foreigners Act, 1946]] and [[Disaster Management Act, 2005]], and asked the DGPs of respective states and union territories to initiate legal action against them.<ref>{{cite news |title=960 foreigners linked to Tablighi Jamaat blacklisted, visas cancelled by MHA |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/foreigners-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-blacklisted-visas-cancelled-by-mha-1662648-2020-04-02 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref>\n\nThe Delhi government ordered an FIR against Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi, the head of Nizamuddin faction of the Tablighi Jamat.<ref name=\"standard\">{{cite news |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/current-affairs/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-120033100007_1.html |newspaper=Business Standard India |publisher=[[Business Standard]] |date=30 March 2020|author=PTI }}</ref><ref name=\"indiatoday\">{{cite web |title=Nizamuddin congregation: Arvind Kejriwal orders FIR against maulana |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/nizamuddin-congregation-arvind-kejriwal-orders-fir-against-maulana-1661514-2020-03-30 |website=India Today |accessdate=30 March 2020}}</ref> After Kandhlawi and five associates named in the FIR went missing, the Crime Branch began conducting raids on possible hideouts in Delhi and Uttar Pradesh.<ref>{{cite news |title=Cops carry out raids to nab Tablighi head |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/apr/02/cops-carry-out-raids-to-nab-tablighi-head-2124565.html |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nThe Delhi Police launched an investigation into a leaked audio clip in which Kandhlawi allegedly asked his followers \"to not abide by government/medical guidelines with regards to the coronavirus outbreak.\" He was also heard saying, \"This is not the time when you leave your prayers or meeting people just because doctors are saying. When [[Allah]] has given this disease, then no doctor or medicine can save us.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=It's time to stay in mosques, Allah will save us: Tablighi Jamaat chief told followers in leaked audio |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/it-s-time-to-stay-in-mosques-allah-will-save-us-tablighi-jamaat-chief-told-followers-in-leaked-audio-1662297-2020-04-01 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> A day later, Kandhlawi released an audio message on [[YouTube]] from his hiding, saying, \"I am in self-quarantine in Delhi as advised by the doctors and appeal to all Jamaat wherever they are in the country to follow the directives of the law.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=Coronavirus: Hiding Tablighi Jamaat chief releases audio message, says he is in self quarantine |url=https://scroll.in/latest/958015/coronavirus-hiding-tablighi-jamaat-chief-releases-audio-message-says-he-is-in-self-quarantine |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=Scroll.in}}</ref>\n\nAccording to reports, around 160 attendees who were quarantined at a railway facility in Delhi \"misbehaved\" and \"spat on\" doctors and healthcare personnel who were attending to them. They also allegedly raised objection to the food served and roamed around the facility in violation of the norms of the isolation ward.<ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat attendees misbehave with staffers, spit at doctors at Delhi quarantine units |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/coronavirus-india-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-misbehave-staffers-spit-doctors-delhi-quarantine-units-1662322-2020-04-01 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> Attendees quarantined at a facility in [[Ghaziabad]] reportedly roamed around naked in the facility and made lewd comments and directed vulgar signs at the nurses.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/tabligh-members-undergoing-treatment-not-cooperating-doctors-to-delhi-govt/articleshow/74969727.cms?from=mdr|title=Tabligh members undergoing treatment not cooperating: Doctors to Delhi govt|date=3 April 2020|work=The Economic Times}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Tablighi Jamaat patients making vulgar signs, roaming nude inside hospital: Ghaziabad CMO tells police |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/tablighi-jamaat-patients-making-vulgar-signs-roaming-nude-inside-hospital-ghaziabad-cmo-tells-police-1662659-2020-04-02 |accessdate=4 April 2020 |work=India Today}}</ref> Uttar Pradesh Chief Minister [[Yogi Adityanath]] condemned the actions, called the patients \"enemies of humanity\" and invoked the [[National Security Act (India)|National Security Act]] against them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/ghaziabad/ghaziabad-tabligh-jamaat-members-misbehave-with-nurses-up-govt-to-invoke-nsa/articleshow/74967055.cms|title=Ghaziabad: Tablighi Jamaat members misbehave with nurses; UP govt to invoke NSA|date=3 April 2020|website=The Times of India}}</ref> In [[Bihar]], stones were pelted at police officers who had gone for tracking Tablighi Jamaat attendees.<ref>{{cite news |title=3 held in Bihar's Madhubani for pelting stones at cops tracking Tabligi Jamaat attendees |url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/nation/2020/apr/01/3-held-in-bihars-madhubani-for-pelting-stones-at-cops-tracking-tabligi-jamaat-attendees-2124401.html |access-date=4 April 2020 |work=The New Indian Express}}</ref>\n\nOn 6 April, news sources reported that some television anchors and journalists were being threatened by Tablighi Jamaat members for covering the \"role of Tablighi Jamaat in the spread of coronavirus.\"<ref>{{cite news |title=TV Journos Receive 'Threats' Over Tablighi Jamaat-Coronavirus Report, NBA Expresses Concern |url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/tv-journos-receive-threats-over-tablighi-jamaat-coronavirus-report-nba-expresses-concern-2566227.html |accessdate=6 April 2020 |work=News18}}</ref>\n\nOn 16 April, Kandhlawi was charged with manslaughter over the gathering.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-52306879 |title=India coronavirus: Tablighi Jamaat leader on manslaughter charge over Covid-19|date=16 April 2020  |work=BBC}}</ref> On 23 April 24 Tablighi members hiding at [[Thane]], Maharastra, were arrested by the crime branch 21 out of the 24 were foreigners from Bangladesh and  Malaysia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/thane/thane-21-foreigners-who-had-attended-tablighi-meet-arrested/articleshow/75325950.cms |title=Thane: 21 foreigners who had attended Tablighi meet arrested &#124; Thane News |work=Times of India |date=23 April 2020}}</ref> Delhi police's crime branch on 23 April raided Maulana Muhammad Saad Kandhlawi's farmhouse at [[Shamli]], [[Uttar Pradesh]].\n\nOn 27 April, 10 of 12 Indonesian Tablighi members who had attended the meet at Delhi were arrested in Mumbai by the [[Mumbai Police]] under [[Indian Penal Code|IPC]] Section 269 (negligent act likely to spread infection of disease that is dangerous to life), Section 270 (Malignant act likely to spread infection of disease dangerous to life) and Section 188 (Disobedience to order duly promulgated by public servant) for not following lockdown rules and visiting mosques.<ref> {{Cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/10-indonesian-nationals-who-attended-tablighi-jammat-at-nizamuddin-held/story-dPOC4TSYxjcI7kHUb0qKsM.html|title=10 Indonesian nationals who attended Tablighi Jamaat at Nizamuddin held|date=2020-04-27|website=Hindustan Times|language=en|access-date=2020-04-28}} </ref>\n\n===Visa Violations===\n[[Patna Police]] arrested 17 preachers who were found to have used tourist visas to enter India but later indulged in religious preaching activities.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thestatesman.com/india/11-malaysians-among-28-foreign-nationals-jailed-violating-visa-norms-1502877451.html|title=11 Malaysians among 28 foreign nationals jailed for violating visa norms|date=14 April 2020|website=The Statesman}}</ref> The [[Ministry of Home Affairs (India)|Ministry of Home Affairs]] blacklisted and cancelled the tourist visas of around 960 foreign Tablighi Jamaat members for violating visa norms by entering India with a tourist visa but indulging illegally in [[missionary]] work in India.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/bihar-17-foreign-preachers-sent-to-jail-for-violating-visa-norms-during-covid-19-pandemic-1666840-2020-04-14|title=Bihar: 17 foreign preachers sent to jail for violating visa norms during Covid-19 pandemic|first=Amitabh|last=Srivastava|date=14 April 2020|website=India Today}}</ref>\n\n==Cases linked==\n\nAccording health authorities, until 2 April, among 2000 positive cases in India nearly 400 cases epidemiological linkage can be traced to the Tablighi Jamaat cluster.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://theprint.in/india/one-in-indias-five-covid-19-patients-is-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-and-its-delhi-event/393993/ |title=One in India's five Covid-19 patients is linked to Tablighi Jamaat and its Delhi event |last=Yadavar |first=Swagata |date=2 April 2020 |website=ThePrint}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/400-covid-19-cases-with-linkage-to-tablighi-jamaat-found-health-ministry/articleshow/74951562.cms |title=400 COVID-19 cases with linkage to Tablighi Jamaat found: Health Ministry|date=2 April 2020 |website=The Times of India}}</ref> By 3 April 647 cases are reported which are related to this cluster.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/politics-and-nation/647-positive-cases-from-14-states-in-last-two-days-are-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-health-ministry/articleshow/74967407.cms |title=647 coronavirus positive cases from 14 states in last two days are linked to Tablighi Jamaat: Health Ministry |date=3 April 2020 |work=The Economic Times}}</ref> By 4 April, 1,023 cases with links to this cluster were reported which is about 30% of total cases in the country.<ref name=\"PTI 4 April\">{{cite news |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/india/story/covid-19-positive-cases-links-tablighi-jamaat-reported-17-states-health-ministry-1663313-2020-04-04 |title=1,023 Covid-19 positive cases with links to Tablighi Jamaat reported from 17 states: Health ministry |agency=Press Trust of India |website=India Today |date=4 April 2020}}</ref> On 18 April, Union Health Ministry said 4,291  out of 14,378 confirmed cases in 23 Indian states and union territories have been linked to this event, around a third of all cases.<ref name=\"ABP 18 April\"/><ref name=\"PTI 18 April\"/>\n\nFollowing are some of the positive cases from different states as reported in media.\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!State or UT\n!Positive Cases\n!Deaths\n!Ref(s)\n|-\n|[[Andaman and Nicobar Islands]]\n|9\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref name=\"ToI400Linkage2Apr\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/400-covid-19-cases-with-linkage-to-tablighi-jamaat-found-health-ministry/articleshow/74951562.cms|title=400 COVID-19 cases with linkage to Tablighi Jamaat found: Health Ministry|date=2 April 2020|website=The Times of India}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Andhra Pradesh]]\n|280\n|1\n|<ref name=\"DainikJagranSpike3Apr\">{{cite web|url=https://english.jagran.com/india/coronavirus-outbreak-295-linked-to-tablighi-jamaat-test-positive-for-covid19-960-foreign-attendees-blacklisted-by-mha-10010317|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Nizamuddin Markaz trail widens with sharp spike in cases in Telangana, Delhi and UP|date=3 April 2020|website=Jagran English}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=ANI|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ani/266-cases-of-coronavirus-in-andhra-pradesh-243-of-them-tablighi-jamaat-attendees-their-contacts-120040601133_1.html|title=266 cases of coronavirus in Andhra Pradesh, 243 of them Tablighi Jamaat attendees, their contacts|date=6 April 2020|work=Business Standard India}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/india-news/steady-rise-in-covid-19-cases-in-andhra-telangana/story-0Up74k9GaTerNL7vETJHKJ.html|title=Steady rise in Covid-19 cases in Andhra, Telangana|date=7 April 2020|website=Hindustan Times|language=en}}</ref>\n|-\n|[[Arunachal Pradesh]]\n|1\n|{{ndash}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.firstpost.com/health/coronavirus-outbreak-arunachal-pradesh-registers-first-covid-19-case-after-31-year-old-tablighi-jamaat-attendee-tests-positive-8219381.html|title=Coronavirus Outbreak: Arunachal Pradesh registers firs